If not for the service this place would likely get 4 or 5 stars. The food is solid and the place is nice. Sydney was nothing short of terrible tonight. She disappeared after taking our initial order and didn't return for almost 30 minutes. There were only 2 other tables occupied inside. So what was Sidney doing? Standing at the corner of the bar with her friends staring at her phone. Meanwhile our drinks were empty. When she finally returned and took our second drink order I caught her just standing at the corner of the bar a few minutes later with her friends staring at her phone again. Hadn't poured a drink. Just standing there. Giggling. At least she had the decency to realize she sucked and bought the round. I hate doing this during covid, but she was beyond lazy and inattentive. I would've gotten another round, but by the time the second one came I asked for the check. Check the place out, but avoid Sydney.
